    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Metal or alloy that is not resistant to oxidation and corrosion in moist air; base metals are thus distinguished from "noble metal." Base metals are also usually of minimum monetary value, and are thus commonly distinguished from "precious metal" as well.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
